{"word":"H7409 - רֶכֶשׁ - rekesh - reh'-kesh - Dromedary","slug":"H7409","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">רֶכֶשׁ</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>rekesh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>reh'-kesh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Dromedary"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E8;&#x05DB;&#x05E9;&#x05C1; - rekesh</b> - <i>reh'-kesh</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/H7408\">H7408</a>; a <i>relay</i> of animals on a post route (as <i>stored</i> up for that purpose); by implication a <i>courser: - </i>dromedary, mule, swift beast."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H7399\">H7399</a>, <a href=\"#/H7408\">H7408</a>"}]}